column2: Document Title: ITP-114-CIV-CPD-Inspection & Test Plan - Horizontal Directional Drilling
ITP created by: Lachlan Morris/Pat Sabaruddin
ITP approved for use by: Pradeep Talasila
1.3 - Plastic Industry Pipe Association - Industry Guidelines
Acceptance Criteria - Conduit Grade PE100, SDR 13.6
3.1 - Check that current revision drawings are being used
Acceptance Criteria - Drawing revison must be confirmed with the design manager
Acceptance Criteria - Auditors are to be VESI accredited
Acceptance Criteria - PE welders are to be qualified and regularly certified by a suitable RTO to PMBWELD301E
Reference - JEMEE-DW-UG-10061100/01, JEMEE-DW-UG-10061100/02, JEMEE-DW-UG-10061100/03, VESI_URD_003; cl5.10.13
Acceptance Criteria - Set out line and level of drilling works.
Method - Set out line and level of drilling works.
○ Survey to mark out existing services.
○ Must maintain a min. clearance as per VESI D&C 5.10.13.
Acceptance Criteria - All conduits must have minimum of one 6mm polypropylene draw rope to AS4142.
Acceptance Criteria - Joints are to be butt welded.
○ Weld map to be supplied and identify unique joint numbers.
○ Butt Welding records to be supplied.
Verifying Documents - Sign ITP, Butt Welding Records
Acceptance Criteria - Location as per current Drill shot plans
Acceptance Criteria - Drill to be installed as per the survey setout.
○ When multiple conduits are installed into one bore hole care shall be taken to ensurethe conduits do not rotate during installation. Accurate detailing of conduit positions must be undertaken.
Frequency - During pilot bore and conduit installation
Acceptance Criteria - Mandrel with 90% of the pipe diameter to be pulled thrugh each conduit to ensure the conduit hasent been compressed.
Verifying Documents - Sign ITP, Visual of pipe pull pictures. Subcontractor Test Record
Acceptance Criteria - All draw ropes must be continious between shafts and have 2m slack in the shaft.
Acceptance Criteria - Auditing to be completed on conduit ends prior to backfilling of entry and exit shafts.
Verifying Documents - Sign ITP, Auditing Report
Acceptance Criteria - Entry pits, exit pits and trenches to be backfilled with Type A or crushed rock. Backfill material shall be compacted to the same density as adjacent material or as specified.
Acceptance Criteria - Acceptance and closeout of subcontractor ITP
Acceptance Criteria - Survey as built report to be compiled.
○ Autocad and PDF reports are to be supplied to:
Acceptance Criteria - All RFIs, NCRs and changes to the IFC drawings are captured on a controlled drawing set marked "Red-line", "As-built" or similar.
Frequency - Once, after construction of the design package

On behalf of Metropolitan Roads Program Alliance, it is hereby certified that the Works represented by the item of work listed have been tested in accordance with the Project Quality Plan and conform in all respects with the requirements of the Contract.
